Number = {23},
Pages = {11-20},
Abstract = {This macro infographic is a set of thematic graphics (12) that add up to
   a scientific-criminalistic informative visual story that was published
   20 years ago in El Peri \& oacute;dico de Catalunya on a double-page
   spread, and has not stopped growing until today. In the first part, the
   work process is presented, from the intellectual to the graphic. The
   narrative line shows a scenario full of contradictions, where US
   President John Fitzgerald Kennedy was assassinated on 22 November 1963.
   It is now 60 years since then. This work has been corrected, retouched,
   changed, reformatted, and updated several times, while preserving the
   ``look{''} of the moment it was made, as a result of participating in
   conferences, debates, symposiums, exhibitions, master classes, and
   conventional classes. The JFK infographics served as a basis for the
   EINA School of Design, for the students of Infographics to produce
   excellent works, which deserved the ``European Newspaper Award{''}, for
   Best Press Infographics 2014. For me, the main scientific principle of a
   good infographic is that visual information is much more easily
   understood and controlled than the same information read in a text, or
   explained orally. And I think that in this case it was achieved. The
   following shows the schemes that structure the global infographic, and
   the analysis of each of the partial graphics, of their infographic
   design tools, and also as carriers of visual informative contents.},
